Manage and Deploy Models in Einstein Discovery

Einstein Discovery uses models to predict outcomes and suggest ways in which to improve predicted outcomes. You can evaluate model quality and compare models before you deploy and manage them.

A model is the sophisticated, custom mathematical construct that Einstein Discovery uses to predict a particular outcome. Create a model and Einstein Discovery generates the predictive and prescriptive analytics.

Model performance metrics reveal quality measures and associated details for a model. Use model performance to evaluate a model's ability to predict an outcome.

Compare metrics for multiple models side by side to see how they stack up against each other.

Deploy a model so that you can use it to make predictions and improvements.

Use the Model Manager to view, configure, and manage prediction definitions and models that have been deployed in your org.
title: Deploying and Managing Predictive Models in Salesforce
